Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 1st time that BTV-12 has been reported in Australia. Please note that the comments made in the epidemiological section of the report provide the full details of this new serotype.

The National Arbovirus Monitoring Program (NAMP) monitors the distribution of economically important arboviruses (i.e., insect-borne viruses) of livestock and their vectors in Australia. For more information on (NAMP) see http://www.animalhealthaustralia.com.au/programs/disease-surveillance/national-arbovirus-monitoring-program/. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3515582,292.]
